==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mesostate
<hw>Mes"o*state</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Meso-</ets>
+ Gr. <?/ to make to stand.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A product
of metabolic action.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Every <xex>mesostate</xex> is either an
<xex>anastate</xex> or <xex>katastate</xex>, according as it is formed
by an anabolic or katabolic process. See <er>Metabolism</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mesosternal</ent>⟦br⟧
